               </tr>
               <tr>
                  <td vAlign="top" colspan="1" align="left"><strong>055</strong></td>
                  <td vAlign="top" colspan="9" align="left"><strong>00</strong><strong>$a</strong>F5449 W4<strong>$b</strong>A28fol. Ref.<br><em>[Multiple 055 fields; Incomplete LC class number and NLC call
                                          number.]</em></td>
               </tr>
            </table>
         </div>
      </div>
      <div class="subfield"><strong>$2 - Source of call/class number</strong> <div class="description">Source list or scheme from which the call/class number was assigned. Used only
                              when the second indicator contains value 6 (Other call number assigned by LAC), 7
                              (Other class number assigned by LAC), 8 (Other call number assigned by the
                              contributing library), or 9 (Other class number assigned by the contributing
                              library).
         </div>
         <div class="description2">
            <div class="description">MARC code that identifies the classification scheme used to assign the call/class
                                 number when the second indicator position contains value 6, 7, 8, or 9.
            </div>
         </div>
         <div class="description2">
            <div class="description">Code from: <em><a href="http://www.loc.gov/standards/sourcelist/classification.html">Classification Scheme Source Codes</a></em>.
            </div>
         </div>
         <div class="example">
            <table width="100%">
               <tr>
                  <td valign="top" width="5%" align="left"></td>
                  <td valign="top" width="10%" align="left"></td>
                  <td valign="top" width="10%" align="left"></td>
                  <td valign="top" width="10%" align="left"></td>
                  <td valign="top" width="10%" align="left"></td>
                  <td valign="top" width="10%" align="left"></td>
                  <td valign="top" width="10%" align="left"></td>
                  <td valign="top" width="10%" align="left"></td>
                  <td valign="top" width="10%" align="left"></td>
                  <td valign="top" width="15%" align="left"></td>
               </tr>
               <tr>
                  <td vAlign="top" colspan="1" align="left"><strong>055</strong></td>
                  <td vAlign="top" colspan="9" align="left"><strong>18</strong><strong>$a</strong>KF385 ZA2<strong>$b</strong>.T34 1989<strong>$2</strong>kfmod<br><em>[Call number assigned from KF Classification, Modified for Use in Canadian
                                             Law Libraries.]</em></td>
               </tr>
            </table>
         </div>
      </div>
      <div class="subfield"><strong>$6 - Linkage</strong> <div class="description">See description of this subfield in Appendix A: <em><a href="http://www.loc.gov/marc/bibliographic/ecbdcntf.html">Control
                                       Subfields</a></em>.
         </div>
      </div>
      <div class="subfield"><strong>$8 - Field link and sequence number</strong> 
        <div class="description">See description of this subfield in Appendix A: <em><a href="http://www.loc.gov/marc/bibliographic/ecbdcntf.html">Control
                                       Subfields</a></em>.
        </div>
   </div>
      <hr>
      <h3>INPUT CONVENTIONS</h3>
      <div class="description2"><strong>Punctuation</strong> - Field 055 does not end with a period.
      </div>
      <div class="description2"><strong>Spacing</strong> - Any spaces that are desired as part of the call number must be input.
      </div>
